				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pet agro was changed a little while ago, owner share pets agro now, and pets still generate alot of agro.
<br />

<br />
So don't think pets are some magic way of lower your agro, if a mob for some reason can't your pet he will summon or rush to pets master instead (this include each time a melee is near and gamerules say he not alowed to attack a pet).
<br />

<br />
Mage agro is rather easy to controll ... Use rains.
<br />
But rains are a really sloppy way, they are useless with adds, they can't be focused (not improve dmg focuesed that is), their range sucks.
<br />
They work, it looks cool (I acctually like the fact that we instead of using shock lets rains land over our enemies .. Fit our profil beter imo), but they are very limited.
<br />

<br />
The fact still remains, in some places I rather totaly stop using Sun Vortex, use it in PoW and you are basicly dead. Last time I used SV in POW was on Offassa .. I slacked at start, MT was still alive, I nuked ONCE with mob at 70% (first nuke), Offassa summoned me, I got spot heals right away and survived 3 rounds, but well .. mages not built to tank 2+ hitters (especially without a CH chain)  so I died, MT survived the whole fight, talk about mob having alot of hate for mages. With Maelstrom+Sun Storm combo I ususally stay alive full time against names.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
