[Tue Nov 11 19:49:31 2003] Terrytigre begins to cast a spell.
<br />
[Tue Nov 11 19:49:31 2003] Derakor the Vindicator says 'Only the strong will survive.'
<br />
[Tue Nov 11 19:49:31 2003] Derakor the Vindicator hits YOU for 450 points of damage.
<br />
[Tue Nov 11 19:49:31 2003] You have been knocked unconscious!
<br />
[Tue Nov 11 19:49:31 2003] You have been slain by Derakor the Vindicator!
<br />
[Tue Nov 11 19:49:34 2003] Returning to home point, please wait...
<br />
[Tue Nov 11 19:49:34 2003] LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...</span>
<br />

<br />
Lorrimar is the Wizard, he got summoned and plummeled about 2 seconds before me Lol  He was using Concussion and I was too.  Oh wait, I don't have that spell, nor anything like it...  Damn!  Know how much mana I had when I got summoned and killed?  ~65%!  Yes, I did 18.6k damage to him (started chaining SV at 95% health, he was at 3% health when he killed me so no biggie) and he summons and plummels me.
<br />

<br />
Same thing happened on Statue of Rallos Zek.  I'm becomming an expert at the WAIT... thing you know kekeke.
<br />

<br />
And BTW, pet keeps his own agro until it dies.  When summoned pet dies, owner inherits all the agro that the pet built up.
<br />

<br />
From what I've heard/experienced, Concussion gets resisted too much on raid mobs anyways.  Some wizards even complain that trash mobs resist it too much.  I'm not sure about A: G. Conc. as I've never used it.[/i]<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=808887" target="_new"><img border=0 src="http://www.iownjoo.com/freeimghost/hornet/Hornet-Sig2.jpg" /></a>
